<zk>
	<div>1. You should see 'test' at second line in textbox and 'changed times: 0' beside it.</div>
	<div>2. Clear the textbox then click on 'changed times: 0', you should see it becomes 'changed times: 1'.</div>
	<div>3. Refresh page.</div>
	<div>4. Delete the first line of textbox then click on 'changed times: 0', you should see it becomes 'changed times: 1'.</div>
	<zscript>
		int i = 0;
	</zscript>
	<window title="new page title" border="normal">
		textbox1: <textbox id="test" rows="4" onCreate='self.setValue("\ntest");'>
					<attribute name="onChange">
						++i;
						lb.setValue("changed times: " + i);
					</attribute>
				</textbox>
		<label id="lb" value="changed times: 0" />
	</window>
</zk>